<p><a name="Adaptations" id="Adaptations"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Primo_Levi&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section: Adaptations">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Adaptations</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><i><a href="/wiki/If_This_Is_a_Man" title="If This Is a Man">If This Is a Man</a></i> was adapted by <a href="/wiki/Antony_Sher" title="Antony Sher">Antony Sher</a> into a one-man stage production <i><a href="/wiki/Primo_(2005_film)" title="Primo (2005 film)">Primo</a></i> in 2004. A version of this production was broadcast on BBC4 in the UK on September 20, 2007.<a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/pressoffice/pressreleases/stories/2007/09_september/13/primo.shtml" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.bbc.co.uk/pressoffice/pressreleases/stories/2007/09_september/13/primo.shtml" rel="nofollow">[6]</a></li>
<li>The 1997 Film <span lang="it" xml:lang="it"><i>La Tregua</i></span> (<i>Truce</i>), starring <a href="/wiki/John_Turturro" title="John Turturro">John Turturro</a>, recounts Levi's long journey home after his liberation from Auschwitz.</li>
</ul>
